      "zh-Hans": "什么时候可以合法地阻塞路口？",
      "zh-Hant": "什麼時候可以合法地阻塞路口？"
    },
    "options": {
      "A": { "en": "During rush hour.", "zh-Hans": "在高峰时段。", "zh-Hant": "在高峰時段。" },
      "B": { "en": "Under no circumstances.", "zh-Hans": "在任何情况下都不可以。", "zh-Hant": "在任何情況下都不可以。" },
      "C": { "en": "If you have a green light.", "zh-Hans": "如果您有绿灯。", "zh-Hant": "如果您有綠燈。" }
    },
    "answer": "B",
    "explanation": { "en": "Never enter an intersection unless there is space to get all the way through.", "zh-Hans": "绝对不可以阻塞路口，即使是绿灯，如果前面没位置让您停下，也不准进去。", "zh-Hant": "絕對不可以阻塞路口，即使是綠燈，如果前面沒位置讓您停下，也不准進去。" },
    "dmv_ref": { "page": "45", "section": "Section 7: Intersections" }
  },
  {
    "id": 115,
    "category": "Literacy",
    "question": {
      "en": "Which of these is true about 'Blind Spots'?",
      "zh-Hans": "关于“盲区（Blind Spots）”，以下哪项是正确的？",
      "zh-Hant": "關於「盲區（Blind Spots）」，以下哪項是正確的？"
    },
    "options": {
      "A": { "en": "Looking over your shoulder is the only way to check them.", "zh-Hans": "回头张望是检查盲区的唯一方法。", "zh-Hant": "回頭張望是檢查盲區的唯一方法。" },
      "B": { "en": "Large trucks have smaller blind spots than cars.", "zh-Hans": "大卡车的盲区比小汽车小。", "zh-Hant": "大卡車的盲區比小汽車小。" },
      "C": { "en": "Mirrors eliminate all blind spots.", "zh-Hans": "后视镜可以消除所有盲区。", "zh-Hant": "後視鏡可以消除所有盲區。" }
    },
    "answer": "A",
    "explanation": { "en": "Mirrors cannot see everything; you must turn your head to check your blind spots before changing lanes.", "zh-Hans": "后视镜有死角，变道前必须扭头看肩膀后方，确认没有车辆。", "zh-Hant": "後視鏡有死角，變道前必須扭頭看肩膀後方，確認沒有車輛。" },
    "dmv_ref": { "page": "63", "section": "Section 8: Scanning" }
  },
  {
    "id": 116,
    "category": "Literacy",
    "question": {
      "en": "If you are under 21, the zero-tolerance law means your BAC cannot be:",
      "zh-Hans": "如果您未满 21 岁，“零容忍”法律规定您的酒精浓度（BAC）不能达到：",
      "zh-Hant": "如果您未滿 21 歲，「零容忍」法律規定您的酒精濃度（BAC）不能達到："
    },
    "options": {
      "A": { "en": "0.01% or higher.", "zh-Hans": "0.01% 或更高。", "zh-Hant": "0.01% 或更高。" },
