  {
    "id": 156,
    "category": "Literacy",
    "question": {
      "en": "2026 Update: Can a single-occupant Electric Vehicle (EV) still use the Carpool (HOV) lane with a Clean Air Decal?",
      "zh-Hans": "2026年更新：单人驾驶的电动汽车（EV）还能凭清洁能源贴纸使用拼车道（HOV）吗？",
      "zh-Hant": "2026年更新：單人駕駛的電動汽車（EV）還能憑清潔能源貼紙使用拼車道（HOV）嗎？"
    },
    "options": {
      "A": { "en": "Yes, until 2027.", "zh-Hans": "是的，直到 2027 年。", "zh-Hant": "是的，直到 2027 年。" },
      "B": { "en": "No, the federal authorization for the CAV decal program expired in late 2025.", "zh-Hans": "不可以，清洁能源贴纸计划的联邦授权已于 2025 年底到期。", "zh-Hant": "不可以，清潔能源貼紙計劃的聯邦授權已於 2025 年底到期。" },
      "C": { "en": "Only on weekends.", "zh-Hans": "仅在周末可以。", "zh-Hant": "僅在週末可以。" }
    },
    "answer": "B",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "As of late 2025/early 2026, single-occupant EVs must follow regular carpool rules unless they have the required number of passengers.",
